  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "PROJECT MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Must have Bachelor’s Degree in Civil Engineering.</li><li>Must have Experience in Building & construction, civil projects.</li><li>Should be completed full cycle of 2 projects.</li><li>Have excellent problem solving skills.</li><li>Minimum 10-15 years of working experience in Singapore as Project manager in large scale building / civil projects, institutional building projects and Community centre projects with main contractor.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare, review, coordinate with clients, consultants, project team members, sub-contractors and all relevant parties to discuss and resolve Project Management, Specifications and Technical Issues.</li><li>Coordinate, monitor & assist the sub-contractors on the progress of work.</li><li>Facilitate the definition of project scope, goals and deliverables.</li><li>Define project tasks and resource requirements.</li><li>Develop full scale project plans.</li><li>Manage project budget.</li><li>Manage project resource allocation.</li><li>Plan and schedule project timelines.</li><li>Track project deliverables using appropriate tools.</li><li>Provide direction and support to project team.</li><li>Quality assurance.</li><li>Constantly monitor and report on progress of the project to all stakeholders.</li><li>Present reports defining project progress, problems and solutions.</li><li>Implement and manage project changes and interventions to achieve project outputs.</li></ul>",
